On 10/15/07, Shubha B S &lt;mailtoshubha@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Hi,
&gt;
&gt; I am using Junit 3.8,
&gt; my objective is &quot;To  get the exact time taken by a test method which should not include setup and teardown time.&quot;
&gt; To achieve this, I have modified junit.framework.TestCase and junit.framework.TestSuite.
&gt;
&gt; in TestCase, I have modified runBare() method
&gt;
&gt;  public void runBare() throws Throwable {
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;                 setUp();
&gt;             try {
&gt;                 //Warm up the test
&gt;     long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
&gt;
&gt;                 runTest();
&gt;             } catch (AssertionFailedError e) {
&gt;                 _failure = true;
&gt;                 // to store the records for functional failure
&gt;                 throw e;
&gt;             }catch (Throwable e) {
&gt;                 _failure = true;
&gt;                 throw e;
&gt;             }finally {
&gt;        System.out.println(&quot;Method Execution taken:&quot; + (System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime))          ;
&gt;                 tearDown();
&gt;             }
&gt;
&gt;     }
&gt;
&gt; this works fine for a testcase like this:
&gt; class validTest extends TestCase{
&gt; public void testValid(){
&gt; calculator.add(10);
&gt; calculator.multiply(10);
&gt; assertEquals(calculator.getResult(), 100);
&gt; }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; But it will not work for a testcase like this
&gt;
&gt; class notWorkingTest extends TestCase{
&gt; public void testNotWorking()
&gt; {
&gt; TestCase success= new TestCase(&quot;success&quot;) {
&gt; protected void runTest() {
&gt; }
&gt; };
&gt; verifySuccess(success);
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; void verifySuccess(TestCase test) {
&gt; junit.framework.TestResult result = test.run();
&gt; assertTrue(result.runCount() == 1);
&gt; }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; Reason being, runBare() method of TestCase is reinvoked. I will end up providing wrong &quot;Method Execution Time&quot;.
&gt; with this logic, for testNotWorking() method,  I will be providing the Execution Time of  &quot;success&quot;.  If have 10 such test.run() invoked from the
&gt; test method, I will be providing time taken for last test.run().
&gt;
&gt; Can anybody provide inputs to solve this problem..
&gt;
&gt; thanks
